  "prompt": "What is the medical condition MDS?",
  "response": "MDS stands for Myelodysplastic Syndromes. These are a group of disorders caused by poorly formed blood cells or ones that don't work properly. The bone marrow, where blood cells are made, doesn't produce enough healthy blood cells, leading to low numbers of red blood cells, white blood cells, and/or platelets. This can cause symptoms such as anemia, tiredness, frequent infections, and easy bleeding or bruising. MDS is more common in older adults and can sometimes progress to acute myeloid leukemia (AML), a type of blood cancer. Treatment depends on the specific subtype of MDS and can include supportive care, medications, and, in some cases, bone marrow transplantation.",
